Assignment Reminder System ðŸ—“

A simple, robust, and persistent command-line application built in Python to help students and professionals track assignments, projects, and deadlines. It uses a JSON file for data storage, ensuring all deadlines are saved between sessions.

## âœ¨ Features

* *Persistent Storage:* All assignments are saved to assignments.json, so your data is secure across multiple runs.
* *Intelligent Reminders:* Alerts you to tasks due within a configurable threshold (default: 3 days).
* *Overdue Flagging:* Clearly identifies any assignments that have passed their due date.
* *Task Management:* Allows you to easily add new tasks and mark completed assignments as deleted.
* *Clean CLI:* Simple, menu-driven command-line interface.

## âš™ Requirements

This project requires *Python 3.6+* and uses only standard, built-in libraries. No external dependencies need to be installed via pip.

* json
* datetime
* time
* os
